<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gallant1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gallant,</orth> subst. a person of rank and mettle: <cit><quote>all the --s of the town,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 101</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>our French --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 22</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>like a g. in the brow of youth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 3, 4</bibl></cit>. Hence == a spruce fellow, a young blood, mostly used ironically: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.413" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 413</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.1.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 1, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.319" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 319</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 126</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 126</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.126" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 126</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.2.212" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 2, 212</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 89</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.198" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.5.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 5, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 7, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 31</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 4</bibl>. Used as a familiar compellation: <cit><quote>--s, I am not as I have been,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 2, 15</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.306" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 306</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 2, 41</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>